Nina Simone was a singular artist, and she went where she pleased, leaving
behind a recorded legacy that is passionate, political, defiant, and delicate
by turns, no matter what strain of folk, blues, jazz, or gospel she was dipping
into, and she did it all with dignity, grace, and intelligence. This set collects
five of her earliest albums, including 1957s Nina Simone and Her Friends, 1959s
The Amazing Nina Simone and Nina Simone at Town Hall, 1960s Nina at Newport, and
1961s Forbidden Fruit, in a single box. Even at the start of her career, Simone
didn't just sing a song -- she made it hers.
